<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-12T17:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-12T17:45:00-05:00" n="961" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d961">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Johnson Electoral Mission/208:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-12T17:00:00-05:45">June 12, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:11 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>105. Department’s June 11, 5 p.m., and last paragraph of my 91, May 29, 3
                            p.m. May I advise this Government at the same time that Captain Johnson
                            will resign the position of President of the National Board of Elections
                            and thus enable this Government to complete the organization of the
                            board? I suggest that the reply be submitted by cable as this Government
                            is anxious to have the board resume its duties as early as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>